t%3BYoung%20people%20are%20struggling%20to%20find%20stable%2C%20relatively%20well-paying%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Creach%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20creating%20a%20lot%20of%20resentment%20or%20frustration%2C%20possibly%20from%20young%20people.%20Instead%20of%20getting%20a%20start%20right%20away%2C%20they're%20punting%20it%20down%20the%20line.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ZipRecruiter%20survey%20found%20that%20over%20half%20of%20tech%20job%20seekers%20age%2025%20to%2034%20and%20nearly%2044%25%20of%20those%20age%2018%20to%2024%20say%20they%20received%20zero%20job%20offers%20in%20the%20past%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FQfRmP%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22young%20cs%20employment%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22324%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EZipRecruiter%20found%20that%20a%20majority%20of%20job%20seekers%20in%20these%20age%20demographics%20say%20they've%20been%20ghosted%20by%20an%20employer%20during%20their%20job%20search%2C%20an%20experience%20that%20has%20become%20more%20common%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-rejected-generation-college-careers-jobs-dating-ghosting-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor%20Gen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Over%2030%25%20of%20them%20say%20their%20job%20search%20is%20going%20%26quot%3Bpoor%26quot%3B%20and%20over%20half%20say%20it's%20just%20going%20%26quot%3Bfair.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreach%20found%20she%20had%20to%20compromise%20her%20job%20expectations%2C%20particularly%20in%20location.%20She%20previously%20had%20all-remote%20roles%20and%20ended%20up%20taking%20a%20job%20that%20required%20going%20to%20an%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20hopes%20to%20eventually%20do%20something%20more%20creative%20in%20her%20career%20or%20move%20into%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20it%20is%20super%20difficult%20to%20get%20a%20job%20for%20those%20remote%20roles%2C%26quot%3B%20Creach%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20think%20about%20how%20I%20could%20start%20getting%20more%20interviews.%20Once%20I%20started%20looking%20at%20more%20jobs%20based%20in%20my%20area%2C%20whether%20hybrid%20or%20fully%20in-office%2C%20I%20started%20to%20get%20more%20responses%20and%20make%20more%20progress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20landed%20his%20current%20job%20after%20three%20to%20four%20months.%20It%20did%20require%20moving%20states%2C%20and%20he%20now%20works%20in%20defense%20tech%20and%20not%20his%20preferred%20industry%2C%20video%20games.%20He%20says%20he's%20trying%20to%20get%20any%20experience%20he%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20dad%20said%20when%20he%20graduated%2C%20it%20was%20difficult%20for%20him%20to%20find%20a%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonathan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20early%2090s%2C%20there%20was%20a%20mini-recession.%20To%20some%20degree%2C%20it%20has%20gotten%20harder%20over%20the%20years%20to%20land%20anything.%20Everyone%20tells%20you%20to%20get%20into%20computer%20science.%20That's%20where%20all%20the%20money%20is%20at%2C%20that's%20where%20the%20jobs%20are%20at.%20It's%20a%20lot%20harder%20than%20they%20make%20it%20out%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b0c411ce-8aa0-49cf-91fd-873aaed2228e%5C%22%3EDon't%20count%20Gen%20Z%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20job%20market%20slowdown%2C%20many%20Gen%20Z%20tech%20workers%20are%20still%20optimistic%20about%20working%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Dobey%2C%2027%2C%20pursued%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%202020%20as%20the%20COVID%20pandemic%20began.%20After%20graduation%2C%20his%20job%20search%20just%20took%20about%20a%20month%20since%20there's%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20lack%20of%20electrical%20engineers%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20lives%20in%20South%20Carolina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20works%20in%20a%20federal%20government%20engineering%20job%20that%20has%20rolled%20back%20hiring%2C%20though%20he%20hasn't%20been%20affected%20by%20cuts.%20Dobey%20said%20his%20friends%20with%20non-engineering%20degrees%20are%20struggling%20more%20to%20find%20work%20than%20his%20peers%20in%20engineering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20might%20not%20all%20be%20in%20our%20dream%20jobs%2C%20but%20they%20are%20doing%20all%20right%2C%20last%20time%20I%20checked.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDobey%20said%20he's%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future%20of%20STEM%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20to%20live%20comfortably%20and%20not%20want%20to%20work%20your%20whole%20life%20like%2C%20be%20a%20doctor%20or%20lawyer%2C%20get%20a%20STEM%20degree%20in%20computer%20systems%2C%20cybersecurity%2C%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264c9c7c7-9698-4b6a-9a8e-025fca3876ef%5C%22%3EJob-seeking%20tips%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDeMase%2C%20the%20ZipRecruiter%20career%20expert%2C%20said%20it's%20important%20for%20tech%20job%20seekers%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20AI%20and%20use%20it%20ethically.%20She%20also%20advises%20using%20their%20network%2C%20getting%20to%20know%20more%20people%20in%20the%20industry%2C%20and%20tailoring%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20to%20better%20align%20with%20target%20roles%2C%20which%20can%20even%20include%20skills%20from%20volunteering%20or%20part-time%20work%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20folks%20think%20about%20the%20roles%20they'll%20apply%20for%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20lean%20into%20their%20strengths%20and%20target%20roles%20that%20are%20hyperaligned%20with%20their%20superpowers%2C%26quot%3B%20DeMase%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20said%20it's%20important%20to%20speak%20clearly%20about%20the%20impact%20they've%20made%20in%20their%20work%20or%20in%20their%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGen%20Z%20approaches%20the%20interview%20as%20an%20interrogation%20rather%20than%20a%20conversation%2C%26quot%3B%20DeMase%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20conversation%2C%20not%20an%20interrogation.%20Come%20prepared%20to%20have%20an%20organic%20chat.%20Don't%20be%20afraid%20to%20remember%20you're%20interviewing%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-entry-level-job-market-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750410002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683f2886ca50259add4d8759%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-entry-level-job-market-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gen%20Z%20graduated%20into%20a%20tight%20tech%20job%20market%3B%20AI%20is%20causing%20big%20shifts%20and%20layoffs.%20They%20still%20seek%20entry-level%20roles%20for%20flexibility%20and%20good%20pay.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmelton%40insider.com%20(Monica%20Melton%2CRosalie%20Chan%2CHugh%20Langley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-entry-level-job-market-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amazon's%20cloud%20business%20is%20revamping%20its%20AI%20app%20strategy%20and%20even%20considered%20sunsetting%20the%20Q%20chatbot%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68199ed2c6ad288d14801a7b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmazon%20CEO%20Andy%20Jassy%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FBrendan%20McDermid%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20plans%20to%20launch%20Q%20Business%20Suite%2C%20a%20new%20AI%20application%20for%20corporate%20users.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EQBS%20will%20unify%20Amazon's%20AI%20tools%2C%20offering%20a%20single%20interface%20for%20data%20analysis%20and%20work%20automation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmazon%20wants%20to%20strengthen%20its%20position%20in%20the%20bus